			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~schneidafunk">schneidafunk</a>  <span class="uid"><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~schneidafunk">( 795759 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64694440"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64694440"><p>Agreed.  Let's use an example unrelated to computers.   Someone discovers a way to break into your house that was not thought about before, an easy way to break a lock.  You need to update your lock ASAP, but in the meantime bad guys have an opportunity to break in.   In the computer world, the time frame is much faster.   This situation is ALWAYS in favor of bad guys.  There needs to be some responsible disclosure process so people have time to update their stuff without letting every bad person in the wor<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64694440">

